  "prompt": "What are some less fictioned movie everyone must watch?",
  "response": "If you're looking for non-fiction films or movies based on true events that are essential viewing, there are several acclaimed documentaries and biographical films that come highly recommended. Here are some you might consider:\n\n1. **Documentaries:**\n   - *13th* (2016) \u2013 Explores the intersection of race, justice, and mass incarceration in the United States.\n   - *Won\u2019t You Be My Neighbor?* (2018) \u2013 A touching look at the life and legacy of Fred Rogers.\n   - *The Act of Killing* (2012) \u2013 A chilling exploration of the Indonesian mass killings of 1965\u201366.\n   - *Bowling for Columbine* (2002) \u2013 Michael Moore\u2019s examination of gun violence in America.\n   - *Man on Wire* (2008) \u2013 Chronicles Philippe Petit\u2019s daring high-wire walk between the Twin Towers in 1974.\n   - *Jiro Dreams of Sushi* (2011) \u2013 Follows an esteemed sushi chef and his dedication to culinary perfection.\n   - *20 Feet from Stardom* (2013) \u2013 Shines a spotlight on the untold true story of the backup singers behind some of the greatest musical legends of the 21st century.\n   - *Citizenfour* (2014) \u2013 Documents Edward Snowden\u2019s NSA leaks.\n   - *Free Solo* (2018) \u2013 Follows rock climber Alex Honnold as he attempts to climb Yosemite's El Capitan without ropes.\n\n2. **Biographical/True Story Films:**\n   - *Schindler\u2019s List* (1993) \u2013 Steven Spielberg's powerful film about Oskar Schindler's efforts to save Jews during the Holocaust.\n   - *A Beautiful Mind* (2001) \u2013 A biographical film about mathematician John Nash and his struggles with mental illness.\n   - *The Social Network* (2010) \u2013 Depicts the founding of Facebook and the ensuing legal battles.\n   - *Hidden Figures* (2016) \u2013 Tells the story of African American female mathematicians at NASA during the Space Race.\n   - *Apollo 13* (1995) \u2013 The gripping true story of the Apollo 13 mission.\n   - *The Pursuit of Happyness* (2006) \u2013 Based on the life of Chris Gardner, a homeless salesman who becomes a successful stockbroker.\n   - *Into the Wild* (2007) \u2013 Chronicles the travels of Christopher McCandless as he explores the Alaskan wilderness.\n   - *The King\u2019s Speech* (2010) \u2013 Focuses on King George VI and his speech therapist.\n   - *Selma* (2014) \u2013 A film about the Civil Rights movement, focusing on the 1965 Selma to Montgomery voting rights marches.\n\nThese films are notable not only for their storytelling but also for the significant issues and historical perspectives they present.",
